USING THE SOFTWARE
In order to use the pycalcal you need:
   * a Python version equal to or greater than 2.5 and less than 3.0.
   * mpmath (http://code.google.com/p/mpmath/)

BUILDING THE SOFTWARE
This project's software is generated following the literate
programming paradigm.
In order generate source code and documentation you need the
following tools:
   * noweb (http://www.cs.tufts.edu/~nr/noweb/)
   * make
   * sh (unix shell)

Unit tests' line coverage metrics are gathered by 'coverage' from
http://nedbatchelder.com/code/coverage/
